Alain Afflelou is also the name of the [[French companies|French]] [[retail chain]] specializing in [[optical]] services and sales of the Alain Afflelou brand of [[eyewear]]. Created in 1972 in [[Le Bouscat]] by Alain Afflelou (the original shop still exists), as of 2007 the company had over 894 stores, 201 of which are in [[Spain]].

In 2006, [[Bridgepoint Capital]], a [[UK]] [[investment firm]], acquired a majority stake in the company.

In 2010, Alain Afflelou Jr., opened his first boutique in [[Milan]] with Luigi J. Zubizarreta, the son of the wealthy businessman Giuseppe Zubizarreta. Alain Afflelou Jr., is the associate of Luigi J. Zubizarreta since 2005.

On 30 April 2012 Bridgepoint Capital announced a period of exclusivity has been offered to [[Lion Capital LLP|Lion Capital]] with the intention of reaching an agreement between Alain Afflelou and Bridgepoint for Lion to acquire the business.

