The '''median alveolar cyst''' is a rare cyst, occurring in the bony [[alveolar bone|alveolus]] between the [[maxillary central incisor]]s.  It is distinguished from a periapical cyst by the fact that adjacent teeth are vital.

==Treatment==
Treatment is by enucleation, or surgical removal.

