{{Infobox university school | name = School of Health and Biomedical Sciences | parent = [[RMIT University]] College of Science, Engineering and Health | image = | head_label = Executive Dean | head = Charlie Xue<ref>[http://www.rmit.edu.au/about/our-education/academic-schools/health-and-biomedical-sciences/contact/people People]. School of Health and Biomedical Sciences, [[RMIT University]]. Retrieved 24 October 2017</ref> | campus = [[RMIT City|City]], Bundoora | affiliations = | website = [http://www.rmit.edu.au/about/our-education/academic-schools/health-and-biomedical-sciences School of Health and Biomedical Sciences] }}
The '''RMIT School of Health and Biomedical Sciences''' is an [[Australia]]n [[tertiary education]] school within the College of Science Engineering and Health of [[RMIT University]]. It was created in 2016 from the former schools of [[RMIT School of Health Sciences|Health Sciences]], [[RMIT School of Life and Physical Sciences|Life and Physical Sciences]] and [[RMIT School of Medical Sciences|Medical Sciences]].
